Commit Message Template for gh-insight-engine
Type of change:
feat:     A new feature
fix:      A bug fix
docs:     Documentation only changes
style:    Changes that do not affect the meaning of the code (white-space, formatting, etc)
refactor: A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
perf:     A code change that improves performance
test:     Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests
chore:    Changes to the build process or auxiliary tools and libraries

Scope (optional):
api:      API changes
ci:       CI/CD changes
db:       Database changes
docs:     Documentation changes
security: Security improvements
deps:     Dependency updates

Subject line (required):
- Use imperative mood ("add" not "added" or "adds")
- Don't capitalize first letter
- No dot (.) at the end
- Max 50 characters

Body (optional):
- Use imperative mood
- Explain what and why vs. how
- Wrap at 72 characters

Footer (optional):
- Reference issues being closed
- Breaking changes

Examples:
feat(api): add user authentication endpoint
fix(ci): resolve npm cache issues in workflow
docs: update README with installation guide
style: format code with prettier
refactor(api): simplify authentication middleware
perf(db): optimize database queries
test: add unit tests for user controller
chore(deps): update dependencies to latest versions